[3] China
Date: Thu 23 Mar 2006
From: Mary Marshall <tropical.forestry@btinternet.com>
Source: Reuters Foundation AlertNet, Thu 23 Mar 2006 [edited]
<http://www.alertnet.org/thenews/newsdesk/PEK136595.htm>

A woman has died of what could be avian influenza in the eastern
Chinese city of Shanghai, state television said on Thursday [23 Mar
2006]. The patient, a 29-year-old female migrant worker, died on
Tuesday [21 Mar 2006] of a pneumonia of unconfirmed origin, an
official at the Shanghai municipality information office told Reuters.
The case is under investigation for bird flu, Shanghai Television
said. China has recorded 15 confirmed cases of bird flu in humans
since late 2005, 10 of whom have died. Doctors and nurses who tended
the patient were under quarantine, said a source at the hospital,
adding final test results were awaited. "It's a suspected case, not
yet confirmed," the source told Reuters.
The Ministry of Health declined immediate comment. The World Health
Organisation said it was investigating. "We are verifying this rumour
at the moment. We are still treating this as a rumour since there is
no confirmation yet," said Aphaluck Bhatiasevi, WHO spokeswoman in Beijing.
