******
[4]
Date: Thu 23 Mar 2006
From: ProMED-mail
Source: Xinhua News Agency, Thu 23 Mar 2006 [edited]
<http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2006-03/24/content_4338503.htm>

A female patient in Shanghai was reported to have died of an
unidentified type of pneumonia on Tuesday [21 Mar 2006] and experts
say it may be the first human bird flu infectious case in the city.
The 29-year-old migrant worker suffered cough and fever and went to
hospital for the first time on 15 Mar 2006.
Shanghai Municipal Health Department organized experts on Wed 22 Mar
2006 to perform multiple tests and analysis on the case and made a
preliminary conclusion that the pneumonia was probably caused by high
pathogenic [H5N1] avian influenza virus. The department said it has
already reported the case to the Ministry of Health, asking the
experts for a further diagnosis. According to the department, people
who have had close contact with the dead patient are receiving
medical inspections, but no infectious symptoms have been detected.
The government have also disinfected places where the deceased
patient had visited.
[Byline: Wang Nan]
